 ECB revamp

London: English cricket will revamp its limited overs set-up after next season, the England and Wales Cricket Board (ECB) has announced here. 

The ECB move, which will see changes made to the C amp;G Trophy and the Totesport league one-day competition, is designed to ensure potential England players receive more ?exposure? ahead of an international call-up. (AFP) 

